owing the instructions as explained in this blog post.<br />\n<br />\nWhen we first launched Windows 10 on ARM in late 2017, the long tail of apps customers needed were dominated by 32-bit-only x86 applications, so we focused our efforts on building an x86 emulator that could run the broad ecosystem of Windows apps seamlessly and transparently. Over time, the ecosystem has moved more toward 64-bit-only x64 apps and we&rsquo;ve heard the feedback that customers would like to see those x64 apps running on ARM64. That&rsquo;s why we are working on expanding the capability of our emulation to include x64 applications and sharing this first preview to gather feedback."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-02-20T13:08:43.000Z","msg":"<strong>Microsoft reportedly working on x64 app emulation for ARM PCs<br />\n13 Nov 2019</strong><br />\nMicrosoft is working on bringing 64-bit app emulation to Windows 10 on ARM, potentially with a debut in a feature update in the <strong>first half of 2021</strong>.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.windowscentral.com/microsoft-reportedly-working-x64-app-emulation-arm-pcs\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.windowscentral.com%2Fmicrosoft-reportedly-working-x64-app-emulation-arm-pcs&d=3nH4Hj8OzEJ%2Fsn4LiTBSOpbpPLVkgxcsq72qYZiHPFQ%3D&h=dc10f234\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.windowscentral.com/microsoft-reportedly-working-x64-app-emulation-arm-pcs</a><br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"dfdcb499d2f9d8b2ab1380262d8469dddcbc24fe","tid":2412530,"uid":109923,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"a133037afae14fa98fbf9c073f469bc1ecdf5ded","tid":2412530,"uid":95096,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"328164a595ec697fdd40dd03031c53fa05abf21f","tid":2412530,"uid":109923,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"90c422bf7ee98b6a1bd354ae3610a9d2105f97b6"